title: Skater’s Quarterly - Vol. 2
description:
Skater's Quarterly - A hot new video magazine on the cutting edge of the skate scene. Produced four times a year, SQ-TV is a fast paced MTV-style music/action video featuring hot pros in street and ramp action combined with highlights of the NSA Pro-Tour.  The Calender of Events and WHAT'S HOT sections will keep you on top of what's happening.

SQ-TV Vol. II Includes: 

-An underground video of John Lucero's wedding!!!

-NSA HIGHLIGHTS: Mt. Trashmore, Ohio skate Invasion, Back to the City (San Francisco), Visalia, San Diego.

-SHUT UP and SKATE Highlights: Dallas, Houston

-Video Clips:  Blockhead, New Deal, Alva- Out of Focus, Eric dressen in Mazatlan, Toxic.

-CLASSIC FOOTAGE: Skateboard Mania, The Dog Bowl, Spinning Wheels.

-Demo-Footage: Transworld "Masters of Gravity".

title: First fLick
description: "This was the first skateboard video I ever made. The video coincided with the loss of my virginity, hence the hidden message in the title. I edited this video every night after I'd go film and, as such, roasted my eyeballs working in the dark. This could also fall under the category of a "Seven Crew" video, whom which I had recently been affiliated with at this point.  Or, perhaps, a promo for the Wetboyz video, which we would put together shortly after this. We premiered this video at the Curly's speak easy in 2003. I was too scared to attend the after party." -Travis Adams
